VALUES ('real-p-1772681591140', 'email', TRUE, 'hard', 'Sarah Chen <s.chen@cascadecare-admin.com>', 'MRN Database Access Restoration — Login Required', 'Robert,

Your Medical Record Number (MRN) database credentials expired during our recent transition to the new CareLink EHR system. To restore your access to patient records, you''ll need to re-authenticate immediately.

Visit [https://cascadecare.com/ehr-reauth](https://cascadecare.com/ehr-reauth) and use your staff username and password to reactivate your access. This is a one-time process required for all clinical and administrative users. Your session will time out after 48 hours if you do not complete re-authentication.

Please note: you will not be able to retrieve patient charts or update clinical notes until this step is complete. If you need assistance, reply directly to this email.

Thank you,
Sarah Chen
EHR System Administrator
Cascade Care Group
[www.cascadecare.com](www.cascadecare.com)', 'authority-impersonation', 'null', null, null, null, null, ARRAY['["your staff username and password to reactivate your access','Your session will time out after 48 hours if you do not complete re-authentication','you will not be able to retrieve patient charts','https://cascadecare.com/ehr-reauth"]']::TEXT[], ARRAY['["The request for staff username and password together on a single form is suspicious — legitimate EHR systems use multi-factor authentication and would not ask both credentials simultaneously in a re-auth flow','The 48-hour timeout creates urgency that pressures the user into action without verification — real system migrations typically allow longer grace periods and send multiple notifications','Blocking access to patient charts is a powerful motivator for clinical staff and is designed to bypass caution — attackers know this will drive compliance','The FROM domain is s.chen@cascadecare-admin.com',' but the signature references cascadecare.com — the attacker registered cascadecare-admin.com as a subdomain lookalike"]']::TEXT[], 'This is a hard phishing email impersonating an internal EHR administrator during a plausible system migration scenario. The attacker uses technical jargon (MRN, CareLink, re-authentication, session timeouts) that sounds authentic to healthcare workers and references a real driver of organizational IT projects — EHR platform transitions. The email leverages the fear of losing access to patient records, which directly impacts clinical workflow. The domain tells the story: FROM is cascadecare-admin.com (a convincing subdomain), but the email signature and portal link reference cascadecare.com. The attacker has registered the subdomain as a lookalike. A player must compare the FROM domain against all domain references in the body text to detect this.', 'generated', 'v1')
ON CONFLICT (card_id) DO NOTHING;

