VALUES ('real-l-1772682121754', 'email', FALSE, 'medium', 'Chen Liu <finance@broadcasters-collective.com>', 'Q1 Production Invoices – Please Review and Approve Freelancer Payments', 'Hi Tom,

I''m sending you the Q1 freelancer payment invoices for your review and approval. These cover all contracted talent, post-production contractors, and technical crew who worked on the news and documentary projects during January through March.

I''ve attached a summary sheet and the full invoice ledger. The summary breaks down payments by project and contractor type. Please review for accuracy—check that names, rates, and hours match your project records.

If everything looks correct, please sign off on the approval form (also attached) and return it to me by end of day Wednesday. Once I have your sign-off, I can process these for payment by Friday.

If you notice any discrepancies—missing names, incorrect rates, duplicate entries—please let me know immediately so I can follow up with the contractor or payroll team.

You can reach me at chen.liu@broadcasters-collective.com or stop by Finance (Building 3, Suite 310) with any questions.

Thank you,
Chen Liu
Finance Manager
Broadcasters Collective
finance@broadcasters-collective.com
(503) 555-0167', NULL, 'null', null, null, null, null, ARRAY['["Q1 freelancer payment invoices for your review and approval','Please review for accuracy—check that names',' rates',' and hours match your project records','sign off on the approval form (also attached) and return it to me by end of day Wednesday"]']::TEXT[], ARRAY['["This is an internal finance communication from a named finance manager using the company domain (broadcasters-collective.com). Freelancer payment approval is a routine business process for media production companies.','The sender provides specific verification information: office location',' phone number',' and direct email. The request is for internal approval within a normal workflow',' not for sensitive credentials or external information.','The deadline is reasonable and business-appropriate (end of week)',' and the sender explicitly invites questions and provides a mechanism to flag discrepancies."]']::TEXT[], 'This is a legitimate internal finance notification regarding Q1 freelancer payment approval. The sender is a named finance manager using the company domain, and the request—reviewing and approving contractor invoices—is routine accounting business in the media and entertainment industry. The email references specific internal projects and systems that the recipient (a project manager or production lead) would be familiar with. A player might flag this because it requests approval and includes financial attachments, but this is normal internal business process, not a phishing attempt. The sender provides clear contact methods and an office location for verification, and explicitly invites questions about any discrepancies.', 'generated', 'v1')
ON CONFLICT (card_id) DO NOTHING;

