Claims Documentation Team', NULL, 'null', null, null, null, null, ARRAY['["have received and filed','Documents Received: 16 October 2024',' 11:23 AM EST','No action is needed from you','expect a status update on your claim within 5–7 business days"]']::TEXT[], ARRAY['["Receipt confirmation with timestamp demonstrates the email is a record of a completed action','Specific date and time of receipt provide a verifiable record','Absence of any request for additional credentials confirms this is a routine acknowledgment','Realistic timeline for next steps demonstrates transparency and prevents impatience-driven vulnerability"]']::TEXT[], 'This is a legitimate claim documentation receipt notification. The email confirms that the policyholder''s submitted documents were received and filed, provides a timestamp and record, and explains what happens next. A player might initially worry that this is phishing because it references a claim, but the email asks for nothing—it only acknowledges what was received. The clear statement that no action is needed and the practical instruction about how to check status confirm this is a routine transactional message.', 'generated', 'v1')
