it@meridianrealty.com', 'authority-impersonation', 'null', null, null, null, null, ARRAY['["mandatory security update','re-enter your credentials','it@meridianrealty.com"]']::TEXT[], ARRAY['["A legitimate system update would never require re-entering credentials via an external link — authentication updates happen within the application itself.','The FROM domain meridianrealty-secure.com does not match the legitimate domain meridianrealty.com shown in the signature.','Threat of account lockout and delayed access creates artificial pressure to bypass verification steps."]']::TEXT[], 'This is a medium-difficulty authority-impersonation phishing email posing as an internal IT system administrator. The attacker uses plausible technical language (system authentication refresh, secure re-registration) and references a real-sounding mandatory process. The domain discrepancy is subtle but present: FROM uses meridianrealty-secure.com while the signature correctly lists it@meridianrealty.com. The attacker exploits fear of access loss and operational disruption to drive compliance. Legitimate IT teams distribute updates through the system itself or use internal single sign-on, never ask for credential re-entry via email.', 'generated', 'v1')
