VALUES ('real-p-1772680378080', 'email', TRUE, 'extreme', 'Michelle Torres <m.torres@broadcastmedia-solutions.net>', 'Copyright Clearance Verification – Urgent', 'Hi Jennifer,

I''m Michelle Torres, Compliance Officer at Broadcast Media Solutions. We''re a content licensing platform used by hundreds of independent producers and networks, and we work with your organisation on music and footage licensing.

We''re conducting an audit of all active licensing agreements due to new regulatory requirements under the Digital Millennium Copyright Act (DMCA). As part of this audit, we need you to verify the contact information and signing authority for your licensing account.

Could you please confirm: (1) the name and email of the person authorised to sign licensing agreements on behalf of your company, (2) their direct phone number, and (3) whether any of those details have changed since your account was set up in 2022?

This is a security measure to ensure that any new licensing agreements or amendments are signed by the correct authorised party. Once we have your confirmation, we''ll update our internal records and send you a summary for your files.

I appreciate your prompt response — we need to close out this audit by end of month.

Michelle Torres
Compliance Officer
Broadcast Media Solutions
www.broadcastmediasolutions.com', 'pretexting', 'null', null, null, null, null, ARRAY['["verify the contact information and signing authority','DMCA audit of all active licensing agreements','name and email of the person authorised to sign licensing agreements"]']::TEXT[], ARRAY['["Request for internal authority and contact information appears procedurally justified by the regulatory compliance audit pretext — it feels like a legitimate compliance check.','Reference to DMCA and regulatory compliance adds institutional weight and creates a sense that this is legally required',' pressuring compliance.','The mention of a specific account history (set up in 2022) shows research and creates the false impression of an established business relationship."]']::TEXT[], 'This is an extreme phishing email using pretexting to gather intelligence about a company''s internal decision-makers and signing authority. The attacker poses as a compliance officer at a licensing platform and creates a plausible DMCA audit scenario. No malicious links or credential requests are present — the attack is reconnaissance and social engineering to identify the right target for a follow-up BEC attack. The email reads as routine business compliance communication. The forensic tell is the FROM domain: m.torres@broadcastmedia-solutions.net uses .net instead of .com, while the website in the signature is broadcastmediasolutions.com. Comparing the FROM domain to the company website referenced in the email reveals the TLD mismatch.', 'generated', 'v1')
ON CONFLICT (card_id) DO NOTHING;

INSERT INTO cards_real (card_id, type, is_phishing, difficulty, from_address, subject, body, technique, secondary_technique, grammar_quality, prose_fluency, personalization_level, contextual_coherence, highlights, clues, explanation, source_corpus, dataset_version)
VALUES ('real-l-1772682066680', 'email', FALSE, 'medium', 'Yuki Tanaka <support@pinnaclewealth.io>', 'Update: Enhanced Security Features Now Available for All Pinnacle Wealth Accounts', 'Hi Marcus,

At Pinnacle Wealth, protecting your financial information is our top priority. We''re writing to let you know about three new security features that are now available on all client accounts — no action required, but you may want to explore them.

Hardware Security Key Support — You can now link a hardware security key (YubiKey, Titan, or Nitrokey) to your Pinnacle Wealth login. This provides the strongest available authentication method for account access. Hardware keys cannot be phished or compromised remotely, making them ideal for high-net-worth clients managing large portfolios.

Managed Multi-Factor Authentication — If you prefer not to use a hardware key, we now offer automated MFA setup through your account dashboard. Choose between SMS, authenticator apps, or push notifications. You can configure different MFA methods for different account actions (login, transfers, withdrawals).

Activity Alerts with Custom Rules — Set custom alerts for any account activity: large transfers, new recipients, changes to beneficiaries, login from new locations, or unusual trading patterns. Our system learns your normal behavior and flags anomalies automatically.

How to Get Started:

Log in to your account at accounts.pinnaclewealth.io and navigate to "Security & Authentication" under Account Settings. You''ll see all three options with setup guides and video tutorials. Most clients complete setup in under five minutes.

These features are available immediately and at no additional cost. They''re designed to complement existing security measures, not replace them.

If you''d like to learn more before implementing, our security team has created a detailed FAQ at pinnaclewealth.io/security-faq. You can also contact our support team at support@pinnaclewealth.io or 1-888-555-0176 (Monday–Friday, 8 AM–6 PM ET).

We remain committed to keeping your wealth secure.

Best regards,
Yuki Tanaka
Security Operations
Pinnacle Wealth Management
3500 Park Avenue, Denver, CO 80202
www.pinnaclewealth.io | support@pinnaclewealth.io

You''re receiving this notification because you''re a Pinnacle Wealth client. To manage your notification preferences, visit pinnaclewealth.io/settings.', NULL, 'null', null, null, null, null, ARRAY['["Log in to your account at accounts.pinnaclewealth.io and navigate to \"Security & Authentication\"','These features are available immediately and at no additional cost','You''re receiving this notification because you''re a Pinnacle Wealth client. To manage your notification preferences',' visit pinnaclewealth.io/settings"]']::TEXT[], ARRAY['["Security update explicitly states no action is required and confirms that features are free — phishing often falsely claims security issues demand immediate action or payment','Users are directed to log in to their own account on the legitimate company domain accounts.pinnaclewealth.io to enable new features — phishing would link to external credential submission pages','All domain references (pinnaclewealth.io',' accounts.pinnaclewealth.io) match the sender domain; no lookalike or suspicious variation"]']::TEXT[], 'This is a legitimate security feature announcement from a wealth management firm. The sender is identified as part of the Security Operations team, and all domain references match the sender domain. The email describes real security enhancements (hardware key support, managed MFA, custom alerts) with specific product details and setup instructions. Critically, the email explicitly states that no action is required and that all features are free — the opposite of phishing, which creates false urgency and demands action. Users are directed to their own account on the legitimate domain to enable features, not to click external links or provide credentials. The notification preferences link is provided. This is standard client communication about security improvements.', 'generated', 'v1')
ON CONFLICT (card_id) DO NOTHING;

