VALUES ('real-l-1772686981435', 'email', FALSE, 'medium', 'Sarah Okonkwo <marketing@litigationassociates.law>', 'Early registration open: Litigation Week 2025 annual conference', 'Hi Chen,

Litigation Associates is thrilled to announce that early registration is now open for Litigation Week 2025 — the nation''s premier annual conference for trial lawyers, litigation professionals, and in-house counsel.

Litigation Week 2025 will take place April 20–23 in Denver, Colorado at the Colorado Convention Center. This year''s theme is "Modern Discovery, Modern Advocacy: Technology, Ethics, and Winning Strategies in 2025."

What to expect:

— 5 days of concurrent programming (CLE-eligible)
— 50+ speakers including judges, leading trial counsel, and expert witnesses
— Networking receptions and firm hosting suites
— Exhibit hall featuring 80+ legal tech and service vendors
— Specialized tracks: Depositions and Discovery, Cross-Examination Mastery, E-Discovery Tools and Trends, Jury Persuasion, and more
— First-time attendee orientation and mentoring program

Early bird pricing (through February 28):
— Full conference pass: $1,095 (regular price $1,495)
— Single-day pass: $395 (regular price $595)
— Student pass: $195 (regular price $295)

Accommodations are limited. We recommend booking your hotel early through our official block at the Hyatt Regency Denver. Use code LW25 for a discounted rate: www.hyattregency.com/litigationweek25

Register for Litigation Week 2025 here: www.litigationassociates.law/lw25-register

Full agenda and speaker bios: www.litigationassociates.law/lw25-agenda

After February 28, standard pricing applies. Please register early to lock in savings and ensure your preferred sessions.

For questions about registration, sponsorships, or the conference program, contact: events@litigationassociates.law or (303) 555-0198.

We look forward to seeing you in Denver!

Best regards,
Sarah Okonkwo
Conference Director
Litigation Associates
1200 17th Street, Denver, CO 80202
www.litigationassociates.law

Manage your event communications preferences: www.litigationassociates.law/preferences', NULL, 'null', null, null, null, null, ARRAY['["Early bird pricing (through February 28): Full conference pass: $1','095 (regular price $1','495)','Register for Litigation Week 2025 here: www.litigationassociates.law/lw25-register','5 days of concurrent programming (CLE-eligible) / 50+ speakers including judges',' leading trial counsel',' and expert witnesses','Manage your event communications preferences"]']::TEXT[], ARRAY['["Conference details are comprehensive and specific (dates',' location',' venue',' themes',' speaker count) — typical of legitimate major event marketing','Early bird deadline with clear price comparison creates legitimate promotional urgency tied to registration',' not account security','Links to registration and hotel accommodations go directly to the sender''s domain','Preferences management link is present and functional"]']::TEXT[], 'This is a legitimate conference promotion from a litigation-focused legal organization. The sender (Sarah Okonkwo, conference director at litigationassociates.law) is announcing registration for a major annual conference. The email includes substantive details: specific dates, location, theme, speaker count and types, specialized tracks, full pricing with early bird discount, and multiple resource links all pointing to the sender''s legitimate domain. The early bird deadline creates promotional urgency (a standard marketing tactic for events), but it''s clearly tied to a discount, not to account security. There''s no credential request or suspicious account-state language. The preferences link confirms regulatory compliance. This is authentic professional event marketing.', 'generated', 'v1')
ON CONFLICT (card_id) DO NOTHING;

