VALUES ('real-p-1772677850983', 'email', TRUE, 'easy', 'Robert Santos <r.santos@lifelineclinic.com>', 'Clinical Staff License Verification', 'Hi Chen,

As part of our annual credentialing audit, all licensed clinicians are required to verify their professional license information. This is mandatory for compliance.

Please access the credentialing portal and confirm your license details:

[https://lifeline-clinical-verify.com/credentials](https://lifeline-clinical-verify.com/credentials)

You''ll need your username and password to log in. The process takes about 10 minutes.

Please complete this by Thursday to avoid any disruption to your schedule.

Best,
Robert Santos
Credentialing Coordinator
Lifeline Clinic
liflineclinic.com', 'hyper-personalization', 'null', null, null, null, null, ARRAY['["annual credentialing audit','confirm your license details','https://lifeline-clinical-verify.com/credentials"]']::TEXT[], ARRAY['["Credentialing audits are routine in healthcare settings',' making this request feel standard and legitimate','The attacker requests login credentials on a fake credentialing portal',' phishing for account access','The domain lifeline-clinical-verify.com is a lookalike; the signature references liflineclinic.com — notice the ''lifline'' vs ''lifeline'' variant',' and the domain mismatch reveals the fraud"]']::TEXT[], 'This is phishing using hyper-personalization anchored in healthcare compliance. The attacker impersonates Robert Santos, a Credentialing Coordinator, a real role in healthcare organizations responsible for verifying clinician licenses. By referencing the annual credentialing audit (mandatory in healthcare), the request feels routine. The deadline creates urgency. The domain tells the story: the link uses lifeline-clinical-verify.com but the signature shows liflineclinic.com — a mismatch indicating a fake portal. The personalization is basic (recipient name and role-appropriate regulatory language), making this easy difficulty.', 'generated', 'v1')
ON CONFLICT (card_id) DO NOTHING;

