VALUES ('real-p-1772686912801', 'email', TRUE, 'hard', 'Priya Nambiar <p.nambiar@talentbridgehr-solutions.com>', 'Updated Direct Deposit Authorization Form — Action Required Before Friday Payroll Run', 'Hi Marcus,

Following the payroll system migration we completed last month with your team, our records team flagged that a small subset of employee banking authorizations didn''t carry over cleanly into the new Workday environment. Your organization falls into that group, and finance has asked us to collect fresh direct deposit authorization forms from affected accounts before the Friday payroll run to avoid any delays in disbursement.

I''ve attached a pre-filled authorization form with the employee data we currently have on file. Please have each flagged employee review their banking details, correct any errors, and sign where indicated. Once complete, you can return the forms to me directly or upload them through your HR portal at talentbridge-hr.com/client-portal.

I know Friday is tight — if you can get these back to me by Thursday at noon, I''ll make sure they''re processed same-day. Don''t hesitate to reach out if anything looks off on the pre-filled information.

Best,
Priya Nambiar
Payroll Integration Specialist | TalentBridge HR Solutions
talentbridge-hr.com | p.nambiar@talentbridgehr-solutions.com', 'pretexting', 'null', null, null, null, null, ARRAY['["p.nambiar@talentbridgehr-solutions.com','before the Friday payroll run to avoid any delays in disbursement','upload them through your HR portal at talentbridge-hr.com/client-portal"]']::TEXT[], ARRAY['["The FROM address uses ''talentbridgehr-solutions.com'' — note the hyphenated ''-solutions'' suffix. The legitimate domain referenced in the body and signature is ''talentbridge-hr.com''. These are two different domains',' not variants of the same one. A real employee would send from talentbridge-hr.com.','The payroll deadline creates artificial urgency',' a hallmark of pretexting. The tight timeline is designed to pressure the recipient into acting before they can verify the request through official channels.','The body references the legitimate company portal at talentbridge-hr.com',' which is a different domain from the sender''s FROM address (talentbridgehr-solutions.com). This mismatch is the key forensic tell — the attacker used the real domain in the body to build credibility while sending from a lookalike domain they control."]']::TEXT[], 'This is a payroll pretexting attack. The attacker impersonates an HR integration specialist, constructs a believable narrative around a recent system migration, and requests that employees submit or correct their direct deposit banking information. The attached form is designed to harvest banking credentials or account details. The key forensic tell is the sender domain: the FROM address uses ''talentbridgehr-solutions.com'' while the body references the legitimate company domain as ''talentbridge-hr.com'' — two different domains. The urgency of the Friday payroll deadline is manufactured pressure to prevent the recipient from pausing to verify the request.', 'generated', 'v1')
ON CONFLICT (card_id) DO NOTHING;

INSERT INTO cards_real (card_id, type, is_phishing, difficulty, from_address, subject, body, technique, secondary_technique, grammar_quality, prose_fluency, personalization_level, contextual_coherence, highlights, clues, explanation, source_corpus, dataset_version)
VALUES ('real-p-1772686786376', 'email', TRUE, 'medium', 'CredentialingDesk <credentialing@medigrant-accreditation.com>', 'Physician License Verification — Response Needed by Friday', 'Dear Dr. Chen,

MediGrant Accreditation Services conducts periodic license verification on behalf of hospital network partners as part of their ongoing credentialing maintenance programs. Your name and NPI number have been matched to an upcoming verification cycle for Brightfield Regional Medical Center, which is your primary credentialing institution on file.

We''re contacting you because one document in your credentialing file — specifically your state medical license renewal confirmation — appears to have an expiration date that predates our records. Before we flag this as an open item in the Brightfield credentialing committee''s next review, we wanted to give you the opportunity to confirm or update the record directly.

You can do this by accessing your physician profile through the link below and uploading a current copy of your license documentation. The portal also allows you to verify or correct any other details currently held in your file.

[Access your MediGrant physician profile](https://physicians.medigrant-accreditation.com/profile/verify)

The credentialing committee meets this coming Monday, so we''d appreciate a response or document upload no later than Friday afternoon. If you have questions or believe this message was sent in error, please contact us at support@medigrantaccreditation.com.

Sincerely,
Credentialing Review Team
MediGrant Accreditation Services | medigrantaccreditation.com', 'fluent-prose', 'null', null, null, null, null, ARRAY['["your state medical license renewal confirmation — appears to have an expiration date that predates our records','physicians.medigrant-accreditation.com/profile/verify','medigrant-accreditation.com"]']::TEXT[], ARRAY['["The claim that a license expiration record is incorrect — framed as a discrepancy the recipient can ''correct'' before a committee review — is a well-constructed pretext. It creates professional concern without using overt alarm language',' nudging the recipient toward action.','The link directs to a subdomain of medigrant-accreditation.com',' which matches the FROM address. However',' both are lookalike domains — the legitimate domain referenced in the body and signature is medigrantaccreditation.com (no hyphen). The attacker controls the hyphenated version.','The FROM domain (medigrant-accreditation.com) differs from the real domain cited in the support email and signature (medigrantaccreditation.com) by the addition of a hyphen. This single character difference is the key forensic tell in an otherwise error-free email."]']::TEXT[], 'This phishing email targets a physician with a credentialing-based pretext — a highly effective scenario in healthcare because credentialing lapses carry real professional consequences. The fluent-prose technique is used throughout; there are no grammar issues, no generic greetings, and the scenario is contextually accurate for the industry. The domain tell is a single hyphen: medigrant-accreditation.com (FROM and link) versus medigrantaccreditation.com (legitimate domain in the support contact and footer). The Friday deadline is a soft urgency mechanism tied to a realistic institutional timeline.', 'generated', 'v1')
ON CONFLICT (card_id) DO NOTHING;

