VALUES ('real-p-1772686730029', 'email', TRUE, 'medium', 'Patricia Hansen <p.hansen@cityofportland-permits.org>', 'Building Permit System Migration – Contractor Access Required', 'Hello Marcus,

As you know, we''re transitioning all contractor licensing records from our legacy CAMS system to the new Civic360 platform over the next two weeks. Your firm, Northpoint Construction Services, has fifteen active permits under your supervision.

To ensure a smooth migration and prevent any disruption to your ongoing projects, we need contractors to verify their credentials in the new system before the cutoff date of October 28th. This is a standard security requirement from our IT department — they want to confirm that each account holder can authenticate properly before we move live data.

Please click here to verify your account: [Verify in Civic360](https://civic360-permits-verify.net/contractor/login) and use your existing username and password. Once you''ve logged in successfully, you''ll see a confirmation page. If you have any issues, reply to this email and I''ll escalate it to our technical team.

Thank you for your cooperation during this transition. We appreciate your patience as we modernize our systems.

Best regards,
Patricia Hansen
BuildingPermits Department
City of Portland
cityofportland-permits.com', 'pretexting', 'null', null, null, null, null, ARRAY['["verify their credentials in the new system','click here to verify your account','use your existing username and password','civic360-permits-verify.net"]']::TEXT[], ARRAY['["Pretexting language establishing a realistic government IT migration scenario to justify credential entry','The URL domain (civic360-permits-verify.net) is a lookalike; the legitimate domain referenced in the signature is cityofportland-permits.com — mismatch signals spoofing','Explicitly asks for existing username and password under the guise of a system migration verification','The lookalike domain uses a plausible Civic360 product name but uses .net instead of the legitimate .com domain"]']::TEXT[], 'This is a medium-difficulty pretexting phishing email. The attacker creates a credible government contractor licensing scenario, uses specific details (contractor firm name, permit count, realistic system names like CAMS and Civic360), and frames credential entry as a mandatory security requirement tied to an IT migration. The ask follows logically from the pretext — contractors would expect to re-verify in a new system. The red flag is the sender''s FROM domain (cityofportland-permits.org) paired with the body reference to cityofportland-permits.com, which do not match — but more critically, the verification URL uses civic360-permits-verify.net, a lookalike that does not match either official domain. A player reading casually will see plausible IT language and a reasonable business scenario. A player checking the domain chain will spot the mismatch and realize the verification link is spoofed.', 'generated', 'v1')
ON CONFLICT (card_id) DO NOTHING;

