VALUES ('real-l-1772680379281', 'email', FALSE, 'medium', 'Priya Sharma <p.sharma@millennialrealty.com>', 'Q2 Rental Market Analysis – Regional Team Meeting Tomorrow 10am', 'Team,

I''ve scheduled our quarterly rental market analysis meeting for tomorrow (March 15th) at 10am in Conference Room B. This session will cover absorption rates, vacancy trends, and competitive rent pricing across our five portfolio regions for Q1.

Please come prepared with any recent lease negotiations or tenant feedback from your assigned markets. I''ll be sharing updated comps data and will need each regional lead to present a two-minute overview of their area''s performance.

The meeting link for our Denver and Austin remote staff is in the shared calendar invite. If you haven''t received the calendar invitation, check your spam folder or reply to this email and I''ll resend it.

This is a mandatory attendance meeting. If you have a conflict, please let me know by 5pm today so we can reschedule your presentation.

Looking forward to seeing the data you''ve gathered.

Best,
Priya Sharma
Regional Operations Director
Millennial Realty Management
p.sharma@millennialrealty.com', NULL, 'null', null, null, null, null, ARRAY['["quarterly rental market analysis meeting','mandatory attendance meeting','If you haven''t received the calendar invitation',' check your spam folder or reply"]']::TEXT[], ARRAY['["Meeting is tied to a legitimate business function (quarterly performance review); sender is a named director and calendar invites are standard workplace practice','Mandatory attendance is normal for leadership-level portfolio reviews; this is a routine business requirement',' not a pressure tactic','Sender provides troubleshooting help for a common email delivery issue (spam folder) and offers a direct support path (reply); this is helpful internal communication',' not a credential trap"]']::TEXT[], 'This is a legitimate workplace meeting notification from a named regional operations director. Priya Sharma is requesting attendance at a quarterly business review — a standard property management function. The email includes specific details: date, time, location, meeting purpose, and what to prepare. The ''mandatory attendance'' language might superficially resemble phishing urgency, but in the context of a quarterly business review from a director, it is proportionate and normal. The sender provides helpful troubleshooting (check spam folder) and a direct contact method for issues. The request is transparent, comes from an internal domain, and has a clear business purpose. No credentials, payments, or sensitive personal data are requested.', 'generated', 'v1')
ON CONFLICT (card_id) DO NOTHING;

