VALUES ('real-p-1772679057322', 'email', TRUE, 'medium', 'Cascade Finance Security <security@cascadefinance-alerts.net>', 'Your Online Banking Access Has Been Temporarily Suspended', 'Dear Marcus,

We''ve detected unusual sign-in activity on your Cascade Finance online banking account. To protect your finances, we''ve placed a temporary hold on your online access while we verify your identity.

This is a routine security measure we apply whenever our fraud detection systems flag activity that doesn''t match your usual patterns. Your funds are safe, but you won''t be able to make transfers or access statements until your identity is confirmed.

To restore your access, please verify your account credentials through our secure portal within the next 24 hours:

[verify your account](https://secure-verify.cascadefinance-alerts.net/identity/confirm)

If you don''t complete verification within this window, your account will remain restricted and you may need to visit a branch in person to resolve the issue.

Thank you for banking with us.

Cascade Finance Customer Security Team
[www.cascadefinance.com](www.cascadefinance.com)
Phone: 1-800-555-0192', 'credential-harvest', 'null', null, null, null, null, ARRAY['["cascadefinance-alerts.net','your account will remain restricted','https://secure-verify.cascadefinance-alerts.net/identity/confirm','www.cascadefinance.com"]']::TEXT[], ARRAY['["The sender''s FROM address uses cascadefinance-alerts.net — a lookalike domain. The legitimate website listed in the signature is cascadefinance.com. These do not match',' and a real bank would always send from its primary registered domain.','Threatening account restriction within 24 hours is a classic pressure tactic designed to override careful thinking. Real banks rarely impose such tight self-service windows without alternative options.','The verification link points to cascadefinance-alerts.net — the same attacker-controlled lookalike domain. Hovering or inspecting this URL confirms it leads nowhere near the real bank''s infrastructure.','The signature lists www.cascadefinance.com as the bank''s website',' but every domain in this email is cascadefinance-alerts.net. That internal contradiction is the key forensic mismatch."]']::TEXT[], 'This is a phishing email using a credential-harvest technique framed as a security hold on the recipient''s bank account. The urgency of a 24-hour restriction window is designed to push the target into clicking the link without carefully inspecting the sender domain. The critical tell is the mismatch between the FROM domain (cascadefinance-alerts.net) and the legitimate domain referenced in the signature (cascadefinance.com). Real financial institutions send account security notifications from their primary verified domain, not from hyphenated alert subdomains.', 'generated', 'v1')
ON CONFLICT (card_id) DO NOTHING;

