VALUES ('real-p-1772677879157', 'email', TRUE, 'easy', 'Apex Broadcast Vendor Relations <vendors@apexbroadcast-global.net>', 'Updated W-9 submission — Apex Broadcast vendor onboarding', 'Hi Robert,

Thank you for your patience during the onboarding process. We''re getting close to finalising the service agreement for your production company''s upcoming contract with Apex Broadcast, and our accounts payable team has flagged one remaining item: we don''t have a current W-9 on file for your entity.

Rather than hold up the contract, our vendor portal makes this straightforward — you can complete and submit the form digitally through the link below. It''s the same process all of our independent contractors go through before first payment.

Submit your W-9 here: [https://vendors.apexbroadcast-global.net/w9/submit](https://vendors.apexbroadcast-global.net/w9/submit)

Once your W-9 is on file, our legal team can countersign the agreement and we''ll be all set for the production start date. If you have any questions about the form or the process, feel free to reach out directly.

Looking forward to working with you,
Samantha Reeves
Vendor Relations Manager
Apex Broadcast | apexbroadcast.com', 'fluent-prose', 'null', null, null, null, null, ARRAY['["apexbroadcast-global.net','Submit your W-9 here: https://vendors.apexbroadcast-global.net/w9/submit','complete and submit the form digitally"]']::TEXT[], ARRAY['["The sender''s domain (apexbroadcast-global.net) differs from the legitimate company domain in the signature (apexbroadcast.com). The addition of ''-global'' and the use of .net instead of .com are both classic lookalike tactics.','The link uses the same attacker-controlled domain (apexbroadcast-global.net) rather than apexbroadcast.com. Any W-9 or tax form portal hosted at a domain that doesn''t match the company''s official website should be treated as suspicious.','W-9 forms contain sensitive tax identification information — name',' address',' and Taxpayer Identification Number. Attackers target W-9 collection flows specifically because the data is valuable for identity theft and financial fraud."]']::TEXT[], 'This phishing email targets a vendor or contractor in the media production space, using a W-9 submission request as the lure. The language is entirely professional and contextually appropriate for a business onboarding workflow. The tell is the domain mismatch: the email comes from apexbroadcast-global.net, while the signature references apexbroadcast.com. Clicking the link and submitting a W-9 would hand the attacker the victim''s full tax identification details, which is a high-value form of identity and financial data theft.', 'generated', 'v1')
ON CONFLICT (card_id) DO NOTHING;

