VALUES ('real-l-1772681600242', 'email', FALSE, 'medium', 'TransCargo Shipping <notifications@transcargo.co.uk>', 'Container #TCGU4829847 departure notice', 'Dear Chen,

This is to confirm that your container has departed from the port of origin and is now in transit. Container and voyage details are below:

Container Number: TCGU4829847
Vessel: MV Meridian Express
Voyage Number: TC-2024-1847
Port of Loading: Port of Shanghai, China
Port of Discharge: Port of Long Beach, USA
Estimated Transit Time: 12 days
Estimated Arrival: November 5, 2024

Shipment Summary:
Commodity: Industrial Machinery Parts
Weight: 18.5 tonnes
Volume: 28 cubic metres
Number of Packages: 47
HS Code: 8483.30

Shipping Costs:
Ocean Freight: $2,400.00
Port Handling: $350.00
Documentation: $75.00
Total: $2,825.00

Your detailed Bill of Lading, packing list, and customs documentation are attached. Please retain these documents for customs clearance upon arrival in the USA. You can track your container in real time at [track.transcargo.co.uk/TCGU4829847](https://track.transcargo.co.uk/TCGU4829847).

Should you have any questions regarding your shipment, customs requirements, or billing, please contact our operations team at ops@transcargo.co.uk.

No action required from you at this time.

TransCargo Shipping Operations', NULL, 'null', null, null, null, null, ARRAY['["Container Number: TCGU4829847','Your detailed Bill of Lading',' packing list',' and customs documentation are attached','No action required from you at this time"]']::TEXT[], ARRAY['["Container number and vessel/voyage details are unique identifiers that confirm a real international shipment','Multiple attachments (BOL',' packing list',' customs docs) are standard and necessary for international freight clearance','Statement of no action needed combined with specific transactional data confirms legitimacy"]']::TEXT[], 'This is a legitimate international container departure notice from TransCargo Shipping. The email contains specific maritime transactional details: a container number, vessel name, voyage number, specific ports of origin and discharge, estimated transit time, arrival date, detailed commodity information with HS codes, weight, and volume. The cost breakdown is itemised, and the email explicitly references attached customs documentation—all standard and necessary for international freight. The sender domain matches the company name, and the tracking link uses that same domain. A player might worry about the large amount ($2,825) or the complexity of maritime terminology, but these are legitimate elements of international shipping notifications. The email requests no credentials, creates no artificial urgency, and explicitly states no action is needed until arrival—all confirming this is a genuine transactional communication.', 'generated', 'v1')
ON CONFLICT (card_id) DO NOTHING;

