VALUES ('real-p-1772686835037', 'email', TRUE, 'easy', 'Michael Tan <m.tan@industrialprocesstech.com>', 'Workplace Safety Training Module Completion', 'Hi Keiko,

Our OSHA compliance officer has notified us that your safety training certification expires in 30 days. To maintain compliance with our manufacturing protocols, you''ll need to complete the updated module covering hazard communication and confined space procedures.

You can access the training here: [safety-industrialtech.com/login](https://safety-industrialtech.com/login). Use your employee ID and the temporary password we''ve sent separately. The module takes approximately 45 minutes to complete.

Please finish this by November 25th so we can update our compliance records before the deadline. Let me know if you have any technical difficulties.

Best,
Michael Tan
Safety & Compliance Manager
Industrial Process Technologies
hr@industrialprocesstech.com', 'fluent-prose', 'null', null, null, null, null, ARRAY['["safety-industrialtech.com/login','Use your employee ID and the temporary password"]']::TEXT[], ARRAY['["The training link uses ''safety-industrialtech.com'' but the signature email is ''industrialprocesstech.com''. The domain is rearranged and includes ''safety-'' prefix',' which doesn''t match the legitimate domain from the signature.','Requesting employee ID credentials through an email-referenced external link is credential collection',' even when framed as routine compliance. The mention of a ''temporary password sent separately'' is designed to make the request seem legitimate."]']::TEXT[], 'This is phishing using fluent-prose. The email covers a realistic manufacturing scenario (OSHA compliance, safety training expiry) with professional tone and no urgency keywords beyond the reasonable compliance deadline. The writing quality is high and the request feels routine. However, the training link (safety-industrialtech.com) does not match the legitimate domain in the signature (industrialprocesstech.com). The credential request is credential harvesting. The natural business context and absence of red-flag language make it deceptively convincing, but the domain mismatch is forensically detectable.', 'generated', 'v1')
ON CONFLICT (card_id) DO NOTHING;

