VALUES ('real-p-1772686796226', 'email', TRUE, 'medium', 'Thornfield Investment Bank <noreply@thornfield-investmentbank.com>', 'Secure Message Waiting: Verify Your Identity to Access', 'Dear David,

You have a new secure message from your Thornfield Investment Bank relationship manager waiting in your encrypted message center. Due to regulatory requirements governing the transmission of financial communications, this message can only be accessed after your identity has been verified.

This is a standard step required each time a secure document or account communication is delivered through our encrypted messaging platform. Simply click the link below, sign in with your Thornfield online banking credentials, and your message will be decrypted and displayed automatically.

[Verify your secure message](https://secure-messages.thornfield-investmentbank.com/inbox/verify)

For your security, this link will remain active for 72 hours from the time this email was sent. After that, please contact your relationship manager directly to have the message resent.

Should you have questions, our Private Banking support team is available Monday through Friday, 8 a.m. to 6 p.m. EST at 1-877-555-0503, or via email at [clientsupport@thornfieldinvestment.com](mailto:clientsupport@thornfieldinvestment.com).

Warm regards,
Thornfield Investment Bank
Private Client Services
[www.thornfieldinvestment.com](https://www.thornfieldinvestment.com)', 'credential-harvest', 'null', null, null, null, null, ARRAY['["thornfield-investmentbank.com','sign in with your Thornfield online banking credentials','https://secure-messages.thornfield-investmentbank.com/inbox/verify','www.thornfieldinvestment.com"]']::TEXT[], ARRAY['["The FROM domain is thornfield-investmentbank.com',' a lookalike of the real domain in the signature',' thornfieldinvestment.com. The attacker inserted a hyphen and the word ''bank'' to create a convincing but distinct domain.','The email explicitly asks the recipient to enter their online banking credentials via a link — a classic credential-harvest signal. The framing as a secure document access step makes the request feel procedurally justified.','The secure message link points to thornfield-investmentbank.com',' the attacker''s domain. A real secure messaging portal at a financial firm would always share the exact same domain as the institution''s main website.','The support email and the website in the signature both use thornfieldinvestment.com',' directly contradicting the sender and link domain of thornfield-investmentbank.com. This mismatch is the key forensic tell."]']::TEXT[], 'This phishing email uses the ''secure message waiting'' lure — a technique common in financial sector phishing — to create a plausible reason for the recipient to enter banking credentials via an email link. The regulatory framing and the encrypted messaging platform narrative give the credential request a convincing procedural wrapper. The domain mismatch is the single forensic anchor: the FROM address and verification link use thornfield-investmentbank.com, while the support email and footer website reference thornfieldinvestment.com. Inspecting the sender domain against the body''s own domain references reveals the fraud.', 'generated', 'v1')
ON CONFLICT (card_id) DO NOTHING;

