VALUES ('real-p-1772680368113', 'email', TRUE, 'medium', 'Jennifer Okonkwo <j.okonkwo@cascade-pharma.com>', 'Pharmacy Inventory Access Update', 'Priya,

I wanted to reach out regarding a process improvement we''re rolling out across all our pharmacy locations. We''ve partnered with a new inventory management vendor to streamline our stock tracking and reduce medication order turnaround times. The system goes live next week.

All pharmacy technicians and managers will need to authenticate with the new platform using their staff ID number and date of birth. This additional security layer ensures that only authorized personnel can access controlled substance records. You can complete this step directly through the link below, which will take you to the vendor''s secure portal where you''ll confirm your identity information.

[cascade-pharma-inventory.net/auth/pharmacy-staff](https://cascade-pharma-inventory.net/auth/pharmacy-staff)

Once authenticated, you''ll receive a temporary access code via email that you can use to log in to the live system. If you have any questions about the process, please let me know.

Best regards,
Jennifer Okonkwo
Pharmacy Operations Manager
Cascade Pharmaceutical Solutions
cascade-pharma.com', 'fluent-prose', 'null', null, null, null, null, ARRAY['["authenticate with the new platform using their staff ID number and date of birth','https://cascade-pharma-inventory.net/auth/pharmacy-staff','confirm your identity information"]']::TEXT[], ARRAY['["Requests for personal identity information (staff ID and date of birth) are sensitive and would typically be handled through secure internal systems or in-person verification',' not through an external link.','The domain cascade-pharma-inventory.net contains the company name but does not match the legitimate domain cascade-pharma.com in the signature. The addition of ''inventory.net'' instead of a .com extension is the domain mismatch that signals this is a lookalike.','The justification for identity verification (accessing controlled substance records) creates urgency and legitimacy',' but the method—via an external vendor portal link—bypasses normal security channels."]']::TEXT[], 'This is a medium-difficulty phishing email using fluent prose. The attacker has constructed a realistic scenario involving a legitimate business process (vendor integration for inventory management) and uses natural, professional language throughout. The phishing mechanism is a credential and personal identity harvesting request embedded in what sounds like standard operational procedure. The domain mismatch (cascade-pharma-inventory.net vs. cascade-pharma.com) is the key tell. The request for sensitive personal data (staff ID and DOB) combined with an external link is suspicious upon reflection, as such sensitive authentication would normally occur through internal systems or in-person.', 'generated', 'v1')
ON CONFLICT (card_id) DO NOTHING;

