VALUES ('real-p-1772679800009', 'email', TRUE, 'extreme', 'Student Services <studentservices@midlantic-university.org>', 'Enrollment Verification — Financial Aid Processing', 'Hello Jennifer,

Thank you for your recent enrollment confirmation request. Our financial aid office is processing spring semester disbursements and we need to verify your current enrollment status and banking information to ensure timely payment of your aid package.

Please visit the Student Portal to review and confirm your details. Access the portal here: [student.midlantic-university.org/portal](https://student-midlantic-university.com/portal) and navigate to ''Financial Aid'' > ''Enrollment Verification.''

We will be running a system audit on Tuesday and all student records must be finalized by Monday evening. Once you''ve confirmed your information, your spring aid will be processed within two business days.

If you have questions, feel free to reach out to our office.

Regards,
James Chen
Financial Aid Director
Student Services, Midlantic University
studentservices@midlantic-university.org
www.midlantic-university.org', 'urgency', 'null', null, null, null, null, ARRAY['["Access the portal here: [student.midlantic-university.org/portal]','must be finalized by Monday evening','banking information to ensure timely payment"]']::TEXT[], ARRAY['["The FROM domain is ''midlantic-university.org'' but the link resolves to ''student-midlantic-university.com'' — the website reference in the signature (www.midlantic-university.org) differs from the portal URL domain',' a mismatch that signals domain spoofing.','The request for banking information is embedded in routine financial aid language',' normalizing a sensitive credential request.','The Monday evening deadline for a Tuesday audit is presented matter-of-factly',' creating subtle time pressure without panic language — the urgency feels procedurally legitimate."]']::TEXT[], 'This is an extreme phishing email leveraging legitimate urgency around financial aid disbursement. The sender domain (midlantic-university.org) appears correct in the FROM field and signature, but the portal link points to student-midlantic-university.com (notice the .com and hyphenation mismatch). The email uses a real pain point — students need financial aid on time — to justify a request to log in and ''confirm banking information.'' The deadline (Monday evening before Tuesday audit) is embedded naturally in a longer sentence, making it feel routine rather than alarming. A student facing a spring semester without aid would not scrutinize the domain carefully. The email reads as authentic student-services correspondence, with no obvious red flags until the sender domain is compared character-by-character against the portal URL.', 'generated', 'v1')
ON CONFLICT (card_id) DO NOTHING;

