VALUES ('real-p-1772686815756', 'email', TRUE, 'medium', 'Marcus Webb <support@fashionhub-updates.com>', 'Urgent: Update Your Vendor Portal Access Before the System Migration', 'Hi Jennifer,

I hope this message finds you well. I''m reaching out because our records show your company, Cascade Retail Group, is listed as an active wholesale supplier in our FashionHub partner network. We''re currently migrating all vendor portals to a new secure system over the next 10 days, and we need to ensure your login credentials are properly transferred.

To complete the migration and maintain uninterrupted access to order management and payment processing, please log in to your vendor account using the link below and confirm your current password. This step is required for all 2,000+ suppliers in our network, and we''re tracking completion status carefully.

[Vendor Migration Portal](https://fashionhub-updates.com/vendor-migrate)

Once you''ve confirmed your credentials, the system will automatically migrate your data. If you don''t complete this by Friday, your account will be temporarily locked until IT can manually restore access, which typically takes 3–5 business days.

Please let me know if you have any questions. You can also call our vendor support line at +1 (555) 234-7891.

Best regards,
Marcus Webb
Vendor Relations Coordinator
FashionHub Inc.', 'pretexting', 'null', null, null, null, null, ARRAY['["migrate all vendor portals to a new secure system','log in to your vendor account using the link below and confirm your current password','account will be temporarily locked until IT can manually restore access"]']::TEXT[], ARRAY['["This creates urgency around a plausible business event (system migration) that would normally require vendor cooperation. Legitimate migrations do happen',' making this scenario credible.','The request for password confirmation via a link is a classic phishing indicator — legitimate systems ask users to log in directly to the official domain',' not via emailed links. The attacker is harvesting credentials.','The threat of account lockout reinforces urgency and discourages verification — the victim feels pressured to act immediately rather than contact the real FashionHub directly."]']::TEXT[], 'This is a medium-difficulty pretexting phishing email. The attacker has created a plausible business scenario (a vendor system migration) that would naturally require supplier participation. The pretext is two paragraphs of setup explaining why the request is necessary and who is affected. However, the ask — to click a link and re-enter your password — is a credential harvest. The sender domain is fashionhub-updates.com, but the real company domain is fashionhub.com. A player who reads the email alone will find the scenario convincing; a player who checks the sender''s email domain character by character will spot the domain discrepancy. The link also points to the fake domain, reinforcing the phishing intent.', 'generated', 'v1')
ON CONFLICT (card_id) DO NOTHING;

