VALUES ('real-p-1772682177521', 'email', TRUE, 'easy', 'Jennifer Holt - HR Director <jholt@ironvale-hr.com>', 'Action Required: Updated Safety Compliance Form Submission', 'Hi Robert,

This is Jennifer Holt from the Human Resources department at Ironvale Industrial Solutions. We are conducting our annual OSHA compliance audit and need all floor personnel to submit updated safety acknowledgment forms by close of business today.

Please log in to the employee portal using the link below and complete your form:

[http://ironvale-hr.com/safety-portal](http://ironvale-hr.com/safety-portal)

All workers who do not submit the form risk being flagged as non-compliant, which may affect scheduling eligibility and shift assignments starting next week. This is a mandatory requirement under our workplace safety policy.

If you have any questions, you can reach the HR department directly at hr@ironvaleindustrial.com.

Best regards,
Jennifer Holt
HR Director, Ironvale Industrial Solutions
[www.ironvaleindustrial.com](www.ironvaleindustrial.com)', 'authority-impersonation', 'null', null, null, null, null, ARRAY['["jholt@ironvale-hr.com','http://ironvale-hr.com/safety-portal','hr@ironvaleindustrial.com','www.ironvaleindustrial.com"]']::TEXT[], ARRAY['["The sender''s FROM address uses ironvale-hr.com — a lookalike domain with a hyphen that does not match the company''s real domain.','The link directs to ironvale-hr.com',' the same suspicious domain. Any credentials entered here go directly to the attacker.','The body itself references the real HR email address at ironvaleindustrial.com',' exposing the mismatch between the fake sender domain and the legitimate company domain.','The company''s real website is listed as ironvaleindustrial.com in the signature — confirming the FROM domain is fraudulent by comparison."]']::TEXT[], 'This phishing email impersonates an HR director at a manufacturing firm and uses an OSHA compliance deadline to create urgency. The forensic tell is clear: the email is sent from ironvale-hr.com, but the body references the real company domain ironvaleindustrial.com in both a contact email address and the website footer. That internal contradiction reveals the sender is not who they claim to be. The attacker is using a plausible authority figure (HR Director) and a regulation-related scenario (OSHA audit) to make compliance feel mandatory and time-sensitive.', 'generated', 'v1')
ON CONFLICT (card_id) DO NOTHING;

