VALUES ('real-p-1772682072914', 'email', TRUE, 'extreme', 'Student Accounts <accounts@northwick-university.edu>', 'Tuition Payment Portal — Account Verification Required', 'Dear Priya,

We are writing regarding your student account at Northwick University. As part of our fall billing cycle, we are conducting a routine audit of all student financial records to ensure accuracy and compliance with our payment processing systems.

Please verify your account information by logging in to the Student Accounts Portal: [accounts.northwick-university.edu/verify](https://accounts-northwick-university.net/verify). Once logged in, please review your contact information, emergency contact details, and payment method on file.

This verification process must be completed by November 1st to ensure your spring semester bill is generated correctly and your account remains in good standing. Any accounts not verified by this date will be flagged for manual review, which may delay bill processing and course registration.

The verification typically takes two minutes. Thank you for your prompt attention.

Best regards,
David Kim
Student Accounts Manager
Northwick University
accounts@northwick-university.edu
www.northwick-university.edu', 'urgency', 'null', null, null, null, null, ARRAY['["log in to the Student Accounts Portal: [accounts.northwick-university.edu/verify]','must be completed by November 1st','delay bill processing and course registration"]']::TEXT[], ARRAY['["The FROM domain is ''northwick-university.edu'' but the portal link resolves to ''accounts-northwick-university.net'' — a .net vs .edu swap that matches the signature website (www.northwick-university.edu) in name only',' revealing domain spoofing.','The consequences (account flag',' delayed billing',' delayed registration) are authentic concerns for students and create genuine urgency without hyperbole.','The November 1st deadline is embedded as a routine detail about bill generation',' not emphasized — urgency is procedural and quiet."]']::TEXT[], 'This is an extreme phishing email using routine financial account maintenance to capture student credentials. The FROM domain (northwick-university.edu) matches the signature, appearing legitimate. However, the portal link points to accounts-northwick-university.net (.net instead of .edu). The email leverages real student concerns — missing a bill or registration deadline — to justify immediate action. The November 1st deadline is embedded naturally as a procedural cutoff for spring semester billing, not highlighted or urgent-sounding. A student who hasn''t yet reviewed their fall bill would feel motivated to comply. The entire email reads as authentic student accounts correspondence. A busy student would click without carefully inspecting the domain. The attacker captures login credentials and gains access to the student''s full account, including payment methods, address, and personal information. Only by comparing the FROM domain and signature domain against the portal URL would a recipient detect the spoofing.', 'generated', 'v1')
ON CONFLICT (card_id) DO NOTHING;

