Your account number is required to retrieve the document. This is a standard security check to protect your privacy.

Thank you for being a valued Sunbelt Power customer.

Sunbelt Power Billing System', 'pretexting', 'null', null, null, null, null, ARRAY['["log in with your username and password','Your account number is required','standard security check"]']::TEXT[], ARRAY['["The FROM domain is sunbelt-power.org',' but the link URL is sunbelt-powe.org (missing the ''r'' in ''power'') — a subtle character omission.','Phishing emails disguised as billing notifications are extremely common; legitimate bills are typically sent as attachments',' not via login links.','Framing a credential request as a ''standard security check'' normalizes the ask."]']::TEXT[], 'This is a phishing email using pretexting. The pretext is a routine bill notification, which is a normal, expected communication from a utility company. The attacker omits a character from the domain name (sunbelt-powe.org instead of sunbelt-power.org), a common typosquatting tactic. The request to log in with credentials and provide the account number is the payload. Legitimate utilities send bills as PDF attachments or direct customers to their existing online portal using the official website, not via suspicious login links.', 'generated', 'v1')
ON CONFLICT (card_id) DO NOTHING;

