VALUES ('real-p-1772686780828', 'email', TRUE, 'hard', 'Robert Hale <r.hale@atlastalentgroup.io>', 'Confidential — Offer Package for David Chen Re: Series Regular Role', 'Hi Nadia,

I wanted to reach out directly before this goes through the full agency workflow, as we''re working against a tight confirmation window on the Obsidian Sky production. Our casting team has finalized an offer for David Chen for a series regular role — eight-episode order, SAG-AFTRA scale plus 20%, and a first-look option on the back-nine. I''d prefer to walk you through the full package before it''s formally issued so you have context for the conversation with David.

I''ve placed the full offer summary and deal memo in our secure talent portal. Given the sensitivity around casting announcements for this project, we''re keeping this off the standard distribution and asking representatives to access it through the direct link below:

[View secure talent portal](https://portal.atlastalentgroup.io/offer?ref=OB-SKY-DC-0039)

You''ll need to log in with your agency credentials to view it. Please do have a look before end of day if you can — the production has a table read scheduled Thursday and they''d like to confirm the cast before then.

Looking forward to talking this through with you, Nadia.

Robert Hale
Head of Casting, Scripted
Atlas Talent Group | atlastalent.com
+1 (310) 555-0509', 'fluent-prose', 'null', null, null, null, null, ARRAY['["portal.atlastalentgroup.io/offer?ref=OB-SKY-DC-0039','log in with your agency credentials to view it','atlastalent.com"]']::TEXT[], ARRAY['["The portal link uses the domain ''atlastalentgroup.io'' — an .io TLD appended to a plausible company name variant. This is a lookalike domain registered by the attacker',' separate from the legitimate company domain.','Requesting agency credentials to view a confidential offer document through a custom portal is the credential-harvesting mechanism. Legitimate talent portals authenticate via established industry platforms (Breakdown Services',' Cast It) or send PDFs through established channels — they don''t create bespoke login flows for individual offers.','The signature names the real company website as ''atlastalent.com'' — without ''group'' and with a .com TLD. The FROM domain ''atlastalentgroup.io'' appends ''group'' and uses .io',' making it a clear lookalike when compared against the signature reference."]']::TEXT[], 'This phishing email is a highly targeted attack on a talent agent, using a confidential casting offer as the lure. The scenario is expertly constructed for the entertainment industry: deal terms (SAG-AFTRA scale, back-nine option), production context (table read deadline), and the sensitivity framing (''keeping this off standard distribution'') all read as authentic. The fluent prose and insider vocabulary make casual scrutiny ineffective. The phishing mechanism is the credential-harvesting portal link using a .io lookalike domain (''atlastalentgroup.io'') that differs from the legitimate ''atlastalent.com'' in the signature — both in the appended ''group'' and the TLD. The soft time pressure from the Thursday table read adds urgency without triggering alarm.', 'generated', 'v1real-l-1772822904352')
ON CONFLICT (card_id) DO NOTHING;

