415-555-0147', NULL, 'null', null, null, null, null, ARRAY['["Your remote access certificate for the Cascade Finance VPN will expire on October 18th','log into the Employee Portal [here](https://portal.cascadefinance.com/vpn-renewal) using your standard credentials','contact the IT Help Desk at ext. 4521"]']::TEXT[], ARRAY['["Expiration date is specific and reasonable for certificate renewal cycles; the sender references Cascade Finance by name and IT operations role',' establishing internal authority','The portal URL matches the legitimate company domain (cascadefinance.com); employees are instructed to use existing credentials they already have',' not to create new ones or change passwords','The help desk extension is a verifiable internal contact point; the sender provides a phone number and extension',' allowing the recipient to confirm via internal directory"]']::TEXT[], 'This is a legitimate IT notification. The sender is a named IT manager using the company''s official domain. The action requested — VPN certificate renewal — is routine and proportionate. The email includes specific dates, an internal portal URL on the correct domain, and a verifiable phone contact. A player might flag this as phishing because it requests action and mentions security systems, but the sender''s role, internal domain, proper signature block, and specific technical details (certificate expiration, internal portal, help desk extension) all confirm this is authentic workplace communication.', 'generated', 'v1')
