VALUES ('real-l-1772682135131', 'email', FALSE, 'medium', 'Aisha Coleman <partnerships@equitytrustbank.com>', 'New Partnership: Equity Trust Bank + Consolidated Wealth Advisors', 'Hello Tom,

We''re thrilled to announce a strategic partnership between Equity Trust Bank and Consolidated Wealth Advisors, two organizations committed to delivering comprehensive financial solutions for high-net-worth clients.

Effective immediately, clients of both firms can now access integrated wealth management services without switching providers or consolidating accounts. Here''s what this partnership enables:

Seamless Account Management — View all your Equity Trust Bank checking, savings, and investment accounts alongside Consolidated Wealth Advisors portfolio management through a single unified dashboard. You maintain complete control over your accounts with either firm — no forced consolidation.

Coordinated Tax Planning — Our teams now collaborate directly on tax-efficient withdrawal strategies, charitable giving structures, and multi-account rebalancing. This eliminates gaps that often cost clients thousands in unnecessary taxes.

Simplified Reporting — Receive one consolidated statement covering all accounts, balances, performance metrics, and tax-relevant transactions. Quarterly meetings with your advisor now include real-time access to your full financial picture.

Dedicated Support — A joint client success team is available during business hours to answer questions about either service and coordinate services between firms.

You don''t need to do anything right now. If you currently use both Equity Trust Bank and Consolidated Wealth Advisors, integration is automatic. If you use only one, you can learn more about how the partnership benefits your situation by contacting your account manager or visiting partnerships.equitytrustbank.com/consolidated.

We''re excited about this partnership and look forward to delivering even better service to you.

Warm regards,
Aisha Coleman
Director of Strategic Partnerships
Equity Trust Bank
555 Financial Plaza, Chicago, IL 60601
partnerships@equitytrustbank.com | 1-877-555-0129
www.equitytrustbank.com

To opt out of partnership announcements, update your preferences at equitytrustbank.com/preferences.', NULL, 'null', null, null, null, null, ARRAY['["Effective immediately',' clients of both firms can now access integrated wealth management services','If you currently use both Equity Trust Bank and Consolidated Wealth Advisors',' integration is automatic','To opt out of partnership announcements',' update your preferences at equitytrustbank.com/preferences"]']::TEXT[], ARRAY['["Partnership announcement includes specific operational benefits (unified dashboard',' tax planning coordination',' consolidated reporting) that are realistic and verifiable — phishing announcements tend to be vague or focus only on urgency','Sender explicitly confirms that integration is automatic and no action is required',' plus provides an optional information link — legitimate business announcements give users control',' not pressure','All domain references (equitytrustbank.com) match the sender domain and footer',' with a clear unsubscribe mechanism for preference updates"]']::TEXT[], 'This is a legitimate partnership announcement from a banking firm. The sender is identified as a Director of Strategic Partnerships, and the domain matches all body references. The content describes realistic partnership benefits with specific operational details (unified dashboard, tax planning, consolidated reporting). Critically, the email states that integration is automatic — no user action required — and offers an optional informational link for those interested in learning more. There is no credential request, no false urgency, and no suspicious language. The unsubscribe option is provided. This is standard corporate communication.', 'generated', 'v1')
