VALUES ('real-l-1772686912051', 'email', FALSE, 'medium', 'David Torres <customer-news@pinnaclegas.com>', 'Winter Energy Efficiency Tips — Save on Your Heating Costs', 'Hello Aisha,

As we head into the coldest months, Pinnacle Gas is sharing practical steps you can take right now to reduce heating costs and improve comfort in your home or business.

Quick wins:
- Seal air leaks around doors, windows, and duct connections — savings of 10–15%
- Set your thermostat 2–3 degrees lower during sleeping hours or when away
- Ensure attic insulation is R-30 or higher; add blown-in insulation if needed
- Have your furnace professionally inspected before peak season
- Use smart thermostats to automate temperature schedules

Pinnacle Gas offers a Home Energy Audit program where certified auditors visit your property, identify efficiency gaps, and provide a detailed improvement plan. The audit costs $99 and typically identifies $500–$2,000 in annual savings. To schedule, visit www.pinnaclegas.com/energy-audit or call 1-800-555-0299.

We also offer financing for approved efficiency upgrades through our partner program. Current promotions include rebates on smart thermostats (up to $300) and insulation installation (10% off). Details and eligibility are at www.pinnaclegas.com/rebates.

For more winter safety tips, including carbon monoxide awareness and space heater best practices, visit our safety hub at www.pinnaclegas.com/safety.

Stay warm and efficient this season!

David Torres
Customer Engagement
Pinnacle Gas
www.pinnaclegas.com
Customer Service: 1-800-555-0299
Monday–Friday, 8 AM–6 PM EST', NULL, 'null', null, null, null, null, ARRAY['["Pinnacle Gas offers a Home Energy Audit program','www.pinnaclegas.com/energy-audit','rebates on smart thermostats (up to $300)"]']::TEXT[], ARRAY['["The sender domain pinnaclegas.com matches all website URLs and contact information throughout the body','The email provides educational content (energy efficiency tips) alongside optional paid services',' typical of utility customer outreach','The call to action is informational — visit a website or call to schedule an audit — not a credential request"]']::TEXT[], 'This is a legitimate customer engagement email from a utility company offering both free energy-saving tips and optional paid services. The sender domain pinnaclegas.com is consistent across the FROM address, all website links, and signature. The email provides genuine value — practical efficiency advice and details about audit programs with transparent pricing ($99 audit cost, specific rebate amounts, financing options). Marketing language is standard ("current promotions," "limited time") and applied to real service offerings, not account security. No credentials are requested, no suspicious domain mismatches exist, and multiple contact methods (website, phone) are provided.', 'generated', 'v1')
