The return credit will be processed once the shipment arrives at the destination warehouse and is verified. This typically takes 5–7 business days after delivery.

If you have questions about your return, please contact our returns team at returns@fastfreight.com.

Best regards,
FastFreight Returns Department', NULL, 'null', null, null, null, null, ARRAY['["Return Shipment ID: FF-7742','Your return receipt and pickup documentation are attached','The return credit will be processed once the shipment arrives at the destination warehouse and is verified"]']::TEXT[], ARRAY['["Unique return shipment ID and RMA reference number confirm a tracked return transaction','Attachment documentation is standard for returns processing and provides proof of pickup','Clear credit processing timeline (5-7 business days) sets realistic expectations and adds credibility"]']::TEXT[], 'This is a legitimate return shipment notification from FastFreight Inc. The email documents a return pickup with specific details: collection date and time, the address where items were collected, weight, a return destination, estimated delivery date, and a unique return tracking number. The financial details are itemised—estimated credit, collection fee, and net credit—all realistic for a returns transaction. The email includes a returns receipt attachment and a clear explanation that the credit will be processed after warehouse verification (5–7 business days). The sender domain matches the company name, and the tracking link uses that same domain. A player might worry about the return credit or the collection fee, but both are standard in logistics returns. The email makes no requests for credentials or sensitive information and explicitly states when the credit will appear—all confirming this is a genuine transactional return notification.', 'generated', 'v1')
