VALUES ('real-l-1772686725198', 'email', FALSE, 'medium', 'Aisha Okonkwo <a.okonkwo@northstatepm.com>', 'Maintenance Ticket System Update — New Mobile App Available', 'Hi everyone,

We''ve launched a new mobile app for our maintenance ticketing system. The app replaces the older web-only interface and makes it much easier to submit, track, and close work orders from the field.

You can download the app from the App Store or Google Play by searching "North State PM Maintenance" or scanning the QR code on the attached setup sheet. Once installed, log in with your same credentials (username and password) that you use on the web portal.

The web portal is still available, so there''s no rush to switch immediately. However, we recommend using the app for new ticket submissions because it integrates with your location data and photo tools — much faster than the old system.

We''ve documented all the changes in our training wiki at [wiki.northstatepm.com/maintenance-app](https://wiki.northstatepm.com/maintenance-app). There''s also a video walkthrough if you prefer that.

If you run into any bugs or have feature requests, please email me directly at a.okonkwo@northstatepm.com or reach out to our IT team at itsupport@northstatepm.com.

Thanks for adapting to the new system — it''ll make our job easier.

Aisha Okonkwo
Maintenance Operations Manager
North State Property Management
(555) 726-5511 ext. 408', NULL, 'null', null, null, null, null, ARRAY['["download the app from the App Store or Google Play','log in with your same credentials','[wiki.northstatepm.com/maintenance-app]"]']::TEXT[], ARRAY['["App distribution through official app stores is standard and secure; the sender provides multiple legitimate download channels','The sender is a named manager with a verifiable title and extension; IT support contact is provided for verification','Wiki link is the company''s internal documentation; users can verify independently without taking action on the first email"]']::TEXT[], 'This is a legitimate internal IT/operations update announcing a new maintenance application. The sender is a named operations manager using the company domain, and the update is routine for property management companies upgrading field-facing tools. The email provides multiple download channels and an alternative web portal, making adoption optional rather than urgent. The sender includes direct contact information and points to internal documentation, allowing employees to verify the update independently.', 'generated', 'v1')
ON CONFLICT (card_id) DO NOTHING;

