VALUES ('real-l-1772822889396', 'email', FALSE, 'medium', 'Carla Martinez <hr@trustinsurance.com>', 'Your 2025 Insurance Enrollment Reminder – Three Days Left', 'Hi Jonathan,

Just a friendly reminder that open enrollment closes this Friday, October 18th at 5:00 PM EST. If you haven''t yet selected your 2025 health, dental, and vision plans, please do so now.

You have three simple steps:
1. Go to [Enrollment Portal](https://enroll.trustinsurance.com) and log in with your employee ID
2. Review the plan options and select your coverage for each category
3. Click ''Confirm and Submit''

Once submitted, you''ll receive an email confirmation with your plan details.

If you have questions about specific plans, the comparison tool on the portal breaks down costs and coverage side by side. For technical issues accessing the portal, contact IT at it-helpdesk@trustinsurance.com or ext. 4100.

Don''t miss this deadline — any elections you don''t make by Friday will default to your current year''s selections.

Let me know if you need anything.

Best,
Carla Martinez
HR Manager
Trust Insurance
hr@trustinsurance.com
Ext. 2750', NULL, 'null', null, null, null, null, ARRAY['["open enrollment closes this Friday',' October 18th at 5:00 PM EST','Go to [Enrollment Portal] and log in with your employee ID','any elections you don''t make by Friday will default to your current year''s selections"]']::TEXT[], ARRAY['["Specific enrollment deadline is clear and urgent but reasonable (three days notice)','Portal login uses existing employee ID',' not a password reset or new credential','Default behavior (keep current selections if no action taken) is transparent and realistic"]']::TEXT[], 'This is a legitimate benefits enrollment reminder from the HR department. Open enrollment is a real annual process, and reminder emails sent as the deadline approaches are standard practice. The sender is an HR manager, the portal is on the company domain, and the login uses employees'' existing ID. The email clearly explains the process, provides deadline context, and offers IT support. While it emphasizes urgency (three days left), that''s appropriate given the actual deadline. This is routine workplace communication.', 'generated', 'v1')
ON CONFLICT (card_id) DO NOTHING;

