support@flexiroute.net', NULL, 'null', null, null, null, null, ARRAY['["out for delivery today between 10:00 AM and 3:00 PM','Pro Number: 987654321','Pallets are insured for $8','500','No action is needed from you at this time"]']::TEXT[], ARRAY['["Specific delivery time window on the day of notification is typical for LTL carriers with real-time fleet tracking and confirms this is a scheduled delivery',' not a phishing attempt','Pro number (bill of lading number) is a unique identifier specific to this shipment that can be independently verified in the carrier''s system','Insurance declaration with specific dollar amount tied to cargo weight and classification shows this is a real goods movement with documented liability','The explicit statement that no action is required',' paired with a service option (reschedule)',' is customer-focused and not designed to manipulate or pressure"]']::TEXT[], 'This is a legitimate same-day delivery notification from an LTL (less-than-truckload) carrier. Aisha is receiving a shipment of three pallets of electronics packaging equipment, and the carrier is confirming pickup from Memphis and delivery to her facility with a specific time window. The email includes the pro number (standard freight bill identifier), freight class, weight, and insurance value — all real logistics data. The sender provides driver information and explains that proof of delivery will be required, which is standard for freight shipments. There is no urgency or credential request, only operational details and a helpful reminder to have staff ready. This is the kind of notification a logistics manager expects when freight is in transit.', 'generated', 'v1')
